PIP:
* PIP is a program to manage external packages or libraries or modules.
* Manage means install, uninstall, upgrade, modify etc.
Note: We use pip3 or pipenv also.
pip sample commands:
1. pip list - to display list of installed packages and there versions.
2. pip install <packagename or modulename> - to install specified module or package.
3. pip uninstall <packagename or modulename> - to uninstall specified module or package.

